oneMinus.$description: Token de Profundidade para nvel negativo interno, usado para dar senso de elementos com contedo interno (como formulrios).

zero.$description: Esse  o token de valor zero para profundidade. Normalmente ele  invocado em todos os componentes que possam usar um componente Box como agrupador. Motivo: isso facilita criar animaes de relevo quando outros agrupadores de nveis diferentes so chamados.

0.$description: Zero spacing - removes all spacing, used for resetting margins/padding

25.$description: Minimal spacing - hairline gaps, subtle borders, tight icon spacing

50.$description: Tiny spacing - compact padding, small gaps between related elements

75.$description: Very small spacing - tight padding for dense layouts, small border radius

100.$description: Small spacing - standard padding for compact components, base unit for spacing scale

125.$description: Small-medium spacing - slightly more breathing room than base unit

150.$description: Medium-small spacing - comfortable padding for small components, form field spacing

175.$description: Medium spacing - standard padding for medium components, card padding

200.$description: Base spacing - default padding for most components, standard gap between elements

225.$description: Medium-large spacing - comfortable padding for larger components

250.$description: Large spacing - generous padding, section spacing, larger gaps

275.$description: Large-medium spacing - between large and extra large, for flexible layouts

300.$description: Extra large spacing - substantial padding, major section gaps, card spacing

350.$description: XL spacing - large component padding, significant section separation

400.$description: 2XL spacing - very large padding, major layout sections, container spacing

450.$description: 2XL-medium spacing - between 2XL and 3XL, for flexible large layouts

500.$description: 3XL spacing - extra large padding, major container spacing, hero sections

550.$description: Touch target size - minimum recommended size for touch interactions (WCAG)

600.$description: 3XL-large spacing - very large padding, major section spacing

700.$description: 4XL spacing - massive padding, large container spacing, feature sections

800.$description: 5XL spacing - huge padding, major layout sections, page-level spacing

900.$description: 6XL spacing - enormous padding, hero section spacing, major page divisions

1000.$description: 7XL spacing - maximum component padding, large hero sections

1200.$description: 8XL spacing - extreme padding, full-page sections, major layout divisions

1400.$description: 9XL spacing - maximum layout spacing, full-page hero sections

1450.$description: 9XL-large spacing - between 9XL and 10XL, for flexible maximum layouts

1600.$description: 10XL spacing - absolute maximum spacing, full-page sections, extreme layouts

scale.$description: Primitive dimension scale. Use semantic tokens for human-readable contexts.

semantic.$description: Human-readable dimension aliases. Use for documentation and foundation contexts.

zero.$description: Zero spacing - removes all spacing, used for resetting margins/padding

pico.$description: Minimal 1px spacing - hairline gaps, subtle borders, pixel-perfect adjustments

nano.$description: Nano spacing (2px) - minimal gaps, tight icon spacing, subtle borders

micro.$description: Micro spacing (4px) - compact padding, small gaps between related elements

extraSmall.$description: Extra small spacing (8px) - base unit for spacing scale, standard compact padding

small.$description: Small spacing (12px) - comfortable padding for small components, form field spacing

medium.$description: Medium spacing (16px) - default padding for most components, standard gap between elements

large.$description: Large spacing (20px) - generous padding, section spacing, larger gaps

extraLarge.$description: Extra large spacing (24px) - substantial padding, major section gaps, card spacing

mega.$description: Mega spacing (28px) - large component padding, significant section separation

giga.$description: Giga spacing (44px) - touch target size, minimum recommended for touch interactions (WCAG)

tera.$description: Tera spacing (72px) - enormous padding, hero section spacing, major page divisions

peta.$description: Peta spacing (116px) - maximum layout spacing, full-page hero sections, extreme layouts

title_1.$description: Use for primary section headers, page titles, and key navigation elements. Title 1 serves as the main title style, drawing the user's attention to the most critical parts of the UI.

title_2.$description: Suitable for secondary section headers, subheadings, and prominent text blocks. Title 2 helps maintain a clear content hierarchy beneath the primary titles.

title_3.$description: Ideal for tertiary headings, category labels, or smaller section dividers. Title 3 is used where space is limited but clarity is still essential.

title_4.$description: Best for minor headings, labels, or descriptive titles where subtle emphasis is required. Title 4 is used to distinguish between different content types while maintaining readability.

highlight_1.$description: Use for key supporting information that needs to stand out beneath a primary title. Highlight 1 is essential for drawing attention to crucial details.

highlight_2.$description: Suitable for secondary supporting text that complements the primary information. Highlight 2 helps to enhance readability without overpowering the main titles.

highlight_3.$description: Ideal for brief explanatory text or annotations that need subtle emphasis. Highlight 3 offers a balance between prominence and subtlety.

highlight_4.$description: Best for minor supporting text or disclaimers that should be noticeable but not distracting. Highlight 4 ensures that all relevant information is accessible without cluttering the UI.

body.$description: Use for primary content text, including descriptions, instructions, and general UI text. The Body style is designed to be easily readable and is the most frequently used text style.

body_large.$description: Use for hightlight content text, chapter or category descriptions, instructions. The Body Large style is a support for Body Large and titles

label.$description: Suitable for indicative labels within forms, settings, or other interface elements where clear, non-interactive text is needed. The Label style is designed to provide clear identification of fields, categories, or statuses.

informative.$description: Ideal for alert messages, notifications, and important instructions. The Informative style ensures that crucial information is immediately recognizable to users.

meta.$description: Best for secondary information such as timestamps, footnotes, or additional context. The Meta style is smaller, providing necessary details without overwhelming the primary content.

quote.$description: Best for secondary information such as timestamps, footnotes, or additional context. The Meta style is smaller, providing necessary details without overwhelming the primary content.

lead.$description: Best for secondary information such as timestamps, footnotes, or additional context. The Meta style is smaller, providing necessary details without overwhelming the primary content.

display_1.$description: Used for the most prominent text elements, such as large headers and impactful banners. It commands attention and conveys the highest level of importance in the hierarchy.

display_2.$description: Ideal for secondary headers or supporting text that requires visibility but less emphasis than Display 1. It balances prominence with readability.

display_3.$description: Serves as a versatile style for subheaders or contextual highlights. It bridges the gap between primary content and less prominent details.

display_4.$description: Designed for smaller banners, captions, or subtle emphasis within layouts. It maintains clarity while supporting a cohesive visual hierarchy.
